cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AR, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper focuses on hardware support for deep convolutional neural networks (CNNs) in computer vision, specifically in mobile and embedded devices. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a new algorithm and implements it in hardware, which falls under the categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AR (Hardware Architecture). Additionally, the paper mentions video compression and motion estimation techniques, which are related to cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
